Job Responsibilities
Develop comprehensive test plans and strategies that cover all aspects of software testing, including functional, performance, security, and usability testing;
Design, implement, and execute test cases, test scripts, and test scenarios;
Perform both manual and automated testing to validate software functionality and performance;
Identify, document, and track software defects and inconsistencies;
Work closely with development teams to reproduce, prioritize, and resolve defects;
Develop and maintain automated test scripts using relevant tools and frameworks;
Integrate automated tests into the continuous integration/continuous deployment (CI/CD) pipeline;
Mentor and guide junior testers, providing training and support to enhance their skills;
Lead testing efforts within the team and ensure adherence to best practices;
Conduct performance and load testing to ensure the application can handle expected user loads;
Perform security testing to identify vulnerabilities and ensure compliance with security standards;
Continuously evaluate and improve testing processes, tools, and methodologies;
Stay updated with the latest industry trends and advancements in testing technologies;
Generate and present detailed test reports, including test coverage, defect metrics, and overall quality assessments;
Provide recommendations for improvements based on test results and analysis.
Job Specifications
The following knowledge, skills, and abilities acquired through a combination of formal schooling, self-education, prior experience, or on-the-job training;
Proficiency in test automation tools and frameworks (e.g., Selenium, JUnit, TestNG, QTP, LoadRunner);
Strong knowledge of scripting languages (e.g., Python, JavaScript) and programming languages (e.g., Java, C#);
Experience with performance and load testing tools (e.g., JMeter);
Familiarity with CI/CD tools and processes (e.g., Jenkins, GitLab CI);
Deep understanding of various testing methodologies, including Agile, Scrum, and DevOps practices;
Expertise in functional, performance, security, and usability testing;
Proficiency in using test management tools (e.g., JIRA, TestRail, Quality Center);
Familiarity with version control systems (e.g., Git);
Strong attention to detail and a high level of accuracy;
Ability to handle multiple projects and priorities simultaneously;
Eagerness to stay updated with the latest testing trends and technologies;
Experience with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure) is a plus;
Effective interpersonal and communication skills;
Good organizational and management skills;
Fluent in both English and Albanian, spoken and written;

